# ── CloudFront WAF (AVD-AWS-0011) ────────────────────────────────────────────
# WAF is not attached. This distribution proxies read-only vanity URLs to
# external platforms that enforce their own security controls. No user input,
# authentication, or sensitive data is handled at this layer. WAF must be
# attached before any application that accepts user input or handles sensitive
# data is added.
AVD-AWS-0011

# ── S3 SSE-KMS (AVD-AWS-0132) ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The default origin S3 bucket uses SSE-S3 (AES256) rather than SSE-KMS.
# This bucket serves a single static holding page (index.html) with no
# sensitive content. The operational overhead of a CMK is not justified here.
AVD-AWS-0132
